// Test fixture for the contract-review Fusion demo.
//
// LEASE_TEXT is a synthetic, professionally-styled residential lease that
// intentionally embeds several hard internal contradictions (conflicting
// concrete numbers/terms placed in non-adjacent sections). It is used to
// confirm that the review panel reliably flags every planted conflict.
//
// All parties, places, and figures are generic and fictional. There are no
// real names, companies, brands, or addresses.

export const LEASE_TEXT: string = `RESIDENTIAL LEASE AGREEMENT

This Residential Lease Agreement (the "Agreement") is entered into as of the Effective Date by and between the property owner ("Landlord") and the undersigned resident ("Tenant"). Landlord and Tenant are referred to collectively as the "Parties." In consideration of the mutual covenants set forth below, the Parties agree as follows.

SECTION 1. PREMISES.
Landlord leases to Tenant, and Tenant leases from Landlord, the residential dwelling unit located within the City of [Placeholder] (the "Property"), together with any fixtures, appliances, and common-area access rights appurtenant thereto. The Property is to be used solely as a private residence for Tenant and the authorized occupants identified in Section 7. Tenant acknowledges having inspected the Property and accepts it in its present condition, subject to Landlord's repair obligations under Section 13.

SECTION 2. TERM.
The initial term of this Agreement shall be twelve (12) months (the "Term"), commencing on the Commencement Date and continuing until the corresponding Expiration Date, unless sooner terminated in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement. Upon expiration of the initial Term, this Agreement shall convert to a month-to-month tenancy unless either Party delivers written notice of non-renewal as provided herein.

SECTION 3. RENT.
Tenant shall pay to Landlord base rent in the amount of Two Thousand Four Hundred Dollars ($2,400.00) per month (the "Rent"), due and payable in advance on the first (1st) day of each calendar month without demand, deduction, or set-off. Rent shall be paid in lawful currency by the method designated by Landlord from time to time. The first month's Rent shall be due upon execution of this Agreement.

SECTION 4. LATE CHARGES.
If any installment of Rent is not received by Landlord on or before the fifth (5th) day of the month in which it is due, Tenant shall pay a late charge of Seventy-Five Dollars ($75.00) as a flat fee for each such delinquent installment. The Parties agree that this flat late charge represents a fair and reasonable estimate of the administrative costs incurred by Landlord as a result of late payment, and it shall be due as additional Rent.

SECTION 5. SECURITY DEPOSIT.
Upon execution of this Agreement, Tenant shall deposit with Landlord the sum of Two Thousand Four Hundred Dollars ($2,400.00) as security for the faithful performance of Tenant's obligations (the "Security Deposit"). Following the termination of the tenancy and Tenant's surrender of the Property, Landlord shall return the Security Deposit, less any lawful deductions, to Tenant within fourteen (14) days, together with an itemized statement describing the basis for any amounts withheld.

SECTION 6. TERMINATION AND NOTICE.
After the initial Term has converted to a month-to-month tenancy, either Party may terminate this Agreement by delivering written notice to the other Party not less than thirty (30) days prior to the intended termination date. Any notice of termination shall specify the effective date and shall be delivered in the manner prescribed by Section 20.

SECTION 7. OCCUPANCY.
The Property shall be occupied only by Tenant and those additional occupants expressly named in this Agreement. The total number of occupants shall not exceed the maximum permitted by applicable housing codes. Tenant shall not permit any other person to reside at the Property for more than fourteen (14) consecutive days without Landlord's prior written approval.

SECTION 8. ASSIGNMENT AND SUBLETTING.
Tenant may sublet the Property or assign this Agreement, in whole or in part, only with the prior written consent of Landlord, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld or delayed. Any approved subtenant or assignee shall be bound by all terms of this Agreement, and Tenant shall remain primarily liable for performance of all obligations hereunder notwithstanding any such sublease or assignment.

SECTION 9. PETS.
Tenant is permitted to keep domestic pets at the Property, subject to a reasonable additional pet deposit and Tenant's agreement to remediate any pet-related damage. Tenant shall ensure that any permitted pet does not create a nuisance or disturb the quiet enjoyment of neighboring residents, and shall comply with all applicable local ordinances concerning animals.

SECTION 10. UTILITIES.
Tenant shall be responsible for arranging and paying for all utilities and services supplied to the Property, including electricity, gas, water, sewer, refuse collection, and telecommunications, except for those services that Landlord expressly agrees in writing to provide. Tenant shall maintain such accounts in good standing throughout the Term.

SECTION 11. METHOD AND AMOUNT OF PAYMENT.
For the avoidance of doubt, the monthly Rent obligation referenced throughout this Agreement is Two Thousand Six Hundred Fifty Dollars ($2,650.00), payable in advance. Landlord may designate electronic transfer, check, or such other commercially reasonable payment method as Landlord may direct. A payment shall be deemed made only when actually received and collected by Landlord in immediately available funds.

SECTION 12. DEFAULT AND REMEDIES.
Tenant shall be in default upon the occurrence of any failure to pay Rent when due or any other material breach of this Agreement. In the event of late payment, Tenant shall pay a late charge equal to ten percent (10%) of the unpaid monthly Rent then due, which the Parties acknowledge as liquidated damages. Upon any uncured default, Landlord may exercise all remedies available at law or in equity, including termination of the tenancy and recovery of possession.

SECTION 13. MAINTENANCE AND REPAIRS.
Landlord shall maintain the structural components, roof, and major building systems of the Property in good and habitable condition and shall make all repairs necessary to keep the Property in compliance with applicable housing and safety codes. Tenant shall keep the interior of the Property clean and sanitary, shall promptly report in writing any condition requiring repair, and shall be responsible for the reasonable cost of correcting damage caused by the negligence or misuse of Tenant, Tenant's occupants, or guests. Tenant shall not undertake repairs at Landlord's expense without Landlord's prior written authorization, except in the case of a bona fide emergency threatening health or safety.

SECTION 14. ANIMALS PROHIBITED.
No animals, pets, or livestock of any kind shall be kept, harbored, or permitted anywhere on or about the Property at any time, whether temporarily or permanently and whether or not a deposit is offered. The presence of any animal on the Property shall constitute a material breach of this Agreement entitling Landlord to pursue all available remedies.

SECTION 15. NO SUBLETTING.
Tenant shall not sublet the Property, in whole or in part, and shall not assign, transfer, or otherwise encumber this Agreement or any interest herein under any circumstances. Subletting and assignment are absolutely prohibited, and any attempted sublease or assignment shall be void and shall constitute an incurable default under this Agreement.

SECTION 16. INSURANCE.
Tenant is encouraged to obtain and maintain a renter's insurance policy covering Tenant's personal property and personal liability. Landlord's insurance does not cover Tenant's personal belongings, and Landlord shall not be liable for any loss of or damage to Tenant's personal property except to the extent caused by Landlord's gross negligence or willful misconduct.

SECTION 17. RETURN OF DEPOSIT.
Within forty-five (45) days after Tenant vacates and surrenders possession of the Property, Landlord shall account for the Security Deposit and refund to Tenant any balance remaining after deduction of amounts properly chargeable under this Agreement and applicable law. Any deductions shall be supported by reasonable documentation made available to Tenant upon request.

SECTION 18. ALTERATIONS.
Tenant shall not make any alterations, additions, or improvements to the Property without Landlord's prior written consent, which Landlord may grant or withhold in Landlord's reasonable discretion. Any approved alterations shall become the property of Landlord upon installation unless otherwise agreed in writing, and Tenant shall not be entitled to compensation for any such improvements upon surrender of the Property. Tenant shall not paint, drill, or affix fixtures to the walls in a manner that causes more than ordinary wear, and shall, upon request, restore any approved alteration to its original condition at Tenant's expense.

SECTION 19. HOLDOVER AND MOVE-OUT.
Should Tenant remain in possession after the end of the tenancy, such holding over shall create a month-to-month tenancy terminable by either Party. To end a month-to-month tenancy, the terminating Party must provide the other Party with written notice of not less than sixty (60) days before the date possession is to be surrendered. Tenant shall return the Property in clean condition, ordinary wear and tear excepted.

SECTION 20. NOTICES AND MISCELLANEOUS.
All notices under this Agreement shall be in writing and shall be deemed delivered when personally delivered, sent by a recognized courier, or mailed by certified mail to the address each Party designates in writing. This Agreement constitutes the entire understanding of the Parties, supersedes all prior agreements, and may be amended only by a writing signed by both Parties. If any provision is held unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect. This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which the Property is located.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have executed this Agreement as of the Effective Date.

LANDLORD: ____________________________

TENANT: ______________________________`;

